column2: HOW LARGE IS THE HIV AIDS *
column5: Nationally there have been over 600#Comma000 people diagnosed with AIDS since 1981. 25% of AIDS cases were linked to injection drug use. An unknown number of Americans are infected with HIV. More about drugs?#Newline<think><set name="topic">drugs</set></think>

column2: DOES HIV * AFFECT ONLY THE USER
column5: No#Comma since an HIV infected user can in turn infect their babies#Comma their sexual partners#Comma and their sexual partners' babies.#Newline <think><set name="topic">drugs</set></think>

Repeated scientific studies say yes. In one study#Comma the average rate of HIV infection was found to decrease by 6% per year in cities with NEPs; the average rate of HIV increased by 6% per year in cities with no NEPs.More about drugs? #Newline<think><set name="topic">drugs</set></think>
